WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:02.670
KATARA: <i>Water...</i>

00:03.460 --> 00:04.760
<i>Earth...</i>

00:05.510 --> 00:06.970
<i>Fire...</i>

00:07.800 --> 00:09.140
<i>Air.</i>

00:09.720 --> 00:13.010
<i>Long ago, the four nations
lived together in harmony.</i>

00:14.140 --> 00:17.940
<i>Then everything changed
when the Fire Nation attacked.</i>

00:18.480 --> 00:21.940
<i>Only the Avatar, master of
all four elements, could stop them.</i>

00:22.070 --> 00:25.690
<i>But when the world
needed him most, he vanished.</i>

00:25.820 --> 00:29.490
<i>A hundred years passed and my brother
and I discovered the new Avatar...</i>

00:29.610 --> 00:31.410
<i>An airbender named Aang.</i>

00:32.080 --> 00:33.740
<i>And although his airbending
skills are great,</i>

00:33.870 --> 00:36.700
<i>he has a lot to learn before
he's ready to save anyone.</i>

00:36.830 --> 00:37.960
AANG: Oof!

00:38.040 --> 00:41.080
<i>But I believe Aang
can save the world.</i>

00:41.540 --> 00:43.290
( â™ª... )

00:46.920 --> 00:49.010
( MAN READING )

00:49.840 --> 00:52.350
You have no idea what this war
has put me through.

00:52.600 --> 00:53.890
Me personally.

00:54.310 --> 00:57.140
The Fire Nation took my mother
away from me.

00:58.180 --> 00:59.350
I'm sorry.

01:00.060 --> 01:03.570
You might have everyone else
here buying your transformation.

01:04.320 --> 01:06.190
But you and I both know
you've struggled with doing

01:06.280 --> 01:07.740
the right thing in the past.

01:07.990 --> 01:10.280
So let me tell you something
right now.

01:10.910 --> 01:14.450
You make one step backward, one slip-up,
give me one reason to think

01:14.530 --> 01:15.910
you might hurt Aang

01:16.540 --> 01:19.370
And you won't have to worry
about your destiny anymore.

01:24.750 --> 01:27.380
( BIRDS CHIRPING )

01:30.010 --> 01:33.010
( SNORING )

01:37.390 --> 01:38.770
( YAWNS )

01:40.640 --> 01:42.310
( APPA GRUNTS )

01:45.570 --> 01:47.440
( APPA GROWLS )

02:09.050 --> 02:10.050
ZUKO: Watch out!

02:10.260 --> 02:11.720
( GRUNTING )

02:11.840 --> 02:13.220
What are you doing?

02:13.300 --> 02:14.720
Keeping rocks from crushing you.

02:15.180 --> 02:18.060
Okay, I'm not crushed,
you can get off me now.

02:18.600 --> 02:20.640
I'll take that as a thank you.

02:23.270 --> 02:25.100
Come on, we can get out
through here.

02:25.360 --> 02:26.520
( MOMO CHATTERING )

02:26.810 --> 02:28.440
( GROANS ) What are you doing?

02:28.980 --> 02:31.110
Go ahead, I'll hold them off.

02:31.610 --> 02:33.400
I think this is a family visit.

02:33.530 --> 02:35.200
Zuko, no!

02:35.320 --> 02:37.490
Come on, we've got to
get out of here.

02:52.470 --> 02:53.930
What are you doing here?

02:54.180 --> 02:56.390
You mean it's not obvious yet?

02:56.510 --> 02:59.310
I am about to celebrate
becoming an only child.

03:04.440 --> 03:06.400
( SHOUTS )

03:32.960 --> 03:34.300
( APPA GROANS )

03:34.510 --> 03:35.930
AANG: I can't get him
to go in there.

03:36.050 --> 03:37.550
Appa hates tunnels.

03:37.890 --> 03:40.560
Aang, there's no way
we can fly out of here.

03:40.970 --> 03:42.640
AANG: We'll have to find a way.

03:43.100 --> 03:44.640
We need to split up.

03:44.770 --> 03:46.980
Take the tunnel and
get to the stolen airship.

03:48.310 --> 03:49.440
No.

03:49.810 --> 03:52.360
The Fire Nation can't
separate our family again.

03:52.610 --> 03:53.990
It'll be okay.

03:54.070 --> 03:55.070
It's not forever.

04:11.250 --> 04:13.840
I can clear that away and
we can fly out through there.

04:13.920 --> 04:17.510
Um, there's an awful lot of fire
in that general direction.

04:17.880 --> 04:18.970
We'll get through.

04:19.090 --> 04:20.090
Let's go.

04:22.600 --> 04:24.060
( APPA GROWLING )

04:34.860 --> 04:36.740
( MOMO CHATTERING )

04:56.630 --> 04:57.840
( APPA GROANS )

04:58.300 --> 04:59.300
( GRUNTS )

04:59.380 --> 05:02.550
( APPA GROANING )

05:21.860 --> 05:23.410
( GRUNTING )

05:24.950 --> 05:27.620
( GRUNTING )

05:30.000 --> 05:31.920
( APPA GROANS )

05:36.000 --> 05:37.800
She's not gonna make it.

05:43.890 --> 05:45.640
Of course, she did.

05:47.310 --> 05:49.680
( APPA GROANS )

05:54.110 --> 05:57.280
AANG: Wow, camping... It really seems like
old times again, doesn't it?

05:57.900 --> 06:01.110
If you really want it to feel
like old times, I could, uh...

06:01.240 --> 06:03.320
Chase you around awhile
and try to capture you.

06:03.450 --> 06:04.490
( LAUGHTER )

06:04.620 --> 06:06.160
Ha-ha.

06:07.120 --> 06:09.620
( SIGHS ) To Zuko.

06:09.750 --> 06:11.790
Who knew after all those times
he tried to snuff us out

06:11.910 --> 06:13.790
today he'd be our hero.

06:14.210 --> 06:15.670
ALL: Hear, hear.

06:16.790 --> 06:17.800
I'm touched.

06:18.090 --> 06:19.260
I don't deserve this.

06:19.670 --> 06:21.420
Yeah, no kidding.

06:23.130 --> 06:24.550
What's with her?

06:24.680 --> 06:26.140
I wish I knew.

06:28.260 --> 06:29.970
SOKKA: What's with him?

06:36.270 --> 06:37.770
This isn't fair.

06:38.020 --> 06:39.690
Everyone else
seems to trust me now.

06:39.860 --> 06:41.030
What is it with you?

06:41.110 --> 06:43.150
Oh, everyone trusts you now?

06:43.280 --> 06:45.570
I was the first person
to trust you, remember?

06:45.820 --> 06:47.280
Back in Ba Sing Se.

06:47.410 --> 06:50.490
And you turned around and
betrayed me, betrayed all of us.

06:51.660 --> 06:53.330
What can I do
to make it up to you?

06:53.870 --> 06:55.120
You really want to know?

06:55.460 --> 06:59.210
Hmm, maybe you could reconquer Ba Sing Se
in the name of the Earth King.

06:59.300 --> 07:02.050
Or, I know, you could
bring my mother back.

07:10.430 --> 07:11.560
Oops.

07:12.060 --> 07:13.230
Wrong tent.

07:13.480 --> 07:15.850
Sorry, do you need to
talk to Sokka too?

07:16.230 --> 07:17.860
Nope, not me.

07:21.900 --> 07:24.530
Well, hello.

07:24.860 --> 07:28.700
Uh, Zuko, yes, why would I be
expecting anyone different?

07:28.820 --> 07:31.200
( GULPS, COUGHS )

07:31.370 --> 07:32.450
So what's on your mind?

07:32.870 --> 07:36.250
Your sister, she hates me,
and I don't know why.

07:36.460 --> 07:38.170
But I do care
what she thinks of me.

07:38.540 --> 07:40.340
Nah, she doesn't hate you.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.090
Katara doesn't hate anyone.

07:42.420 --> 07:44.340
Except maybe some people
in the Fire Nation.

07:44.880 --> 07:48.050
No, I mean, uh, not people
who are good but used to be bad.

07:48.180 --> 07:49.890
I mean bad people.

07:50.140 --> 07:51.640
Fire Nation people who are still bad,

07:51.810 --> 07:53.600
who've never been good
and probably won't be ever.

07:53.680 --> 07:54.680
Stop.

07:55.100 --> 07:56.520
Okay, listen...

07:57.230 --> 07:59.110
I know this may seem
out of nowhere

07:59.610 --> 08:01.690
but I want you to tell me
what happened to your mother.

08:01.980 --> 08:02.980
What?

08:03.190 --> 08:04.400
Why would you want to know that?

08:04.490 --> 08:07.660
Katara mentioned it before when we were
in prison together in Ba Sing Se

08:08.200 --> 08:10.320
and again just now
when she was yelling at me.

08:10.950 --> 08:12.740
I think somehow...

08:13.080 --> 08:16.250
She's connected her anger
about that to her anger at me.

08:17.620 --> 08:19.380
It's not a day I like to remember.

08:26.340 --> 08:28.300
( LAUGHING )

08:34.180 --> 08:36.230
I'm going to find mom.

08:39.020 --> 08:41.480
SOKKA: <i>Many of the warriors had</i>
<i>seen the black snow before</i>

08:41.610 --> 08:43.520
<i>and they knew what it meant...</i>

08:43.650 --> 08:45.440
<i>A Fire Nation raid.</i>

08:45.570 --> 08:47.360
( SCREAMING )

08:51.120 --> 08:52.910
( SCREAMING )

08:56.250 --> 08:59.960
SOKKA: <i>We were badly outnumbered,</i>
<i>but somehow we managed to drive them off.</i>

09:04.340 --> 09:07.090
<i>As quickly as they came,
they just left.</i>

09:10.590 --> 09:12.930
I was so relieved
when it was over

09:13.050 --> 09:15.310
but that's because I didn't
know yet what had happened.

09:16.220 --> 09:18.100
I didn't know
we'd lost our mother.

09:18.480 --> 09:22.440
Wait, can you remember any details about
the soldiers who raided your village?

09:22.860 --> 09:25.020
Like what the lead ship
looked like?

09:25.480 --> 09:27.900
Yeah... Sea ravens.

09:28.070 --> 09:30.490
<i>The main ship had flags
with sea ravens on them.</i>

09:31.030 --> 09:32.820
The symbol of
the southern raiders.

09:33.660 --> 09:34.740
Thanks, Sokka.

09:34.870 --> 09:36.120
No problem.

09:36.240 --> 09:38.450
Thanks for stopping by.

09:38.870 --> 09:40.750
( SIGHS ) Thought
he'd never leave.

09:42.880 --> 09:44.210
Suki?

09:45.880 --> 09:47.710
( WHISTLING )

09:56.350 --> 09:57.720
You look terrible.

09:58.350 --> 09:59.730
I waited out here all night.

09:59.930 --> 10:01.190
What do you want?

10:01.520 --> 10:03.230
I know who killed your mother.

10:03.310 --> 10:04.690
I'm going to help you find him.

10:14.820 --> 10:16.370
I need to borrow Appa.

10:16.950 --> 10:19.830
Why, is it your turn to take
a little field trip with Zuko?

10:20.080 --> 10:21.750
Yes, it is.

10:22.830 --> 10:25.250
Oh... What's going on?

10:25.460 --> 10:28.000
We're going to find the man
who took my mother from me.

10:28.670 --> 10:30.420
ZUKO: Sokka told me
the story of what happened.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.430
I know who did it,
and I know how to find him.

10:33.680 --> 10:36.850
Um, and what exactly do you
think this will accomplish?

10:37.810 --> 10:40.180
( SCOFFS ) I knew
you wouldn't understand.

10:40.720 --> 10:43.270
Wait, stop, I do understand.

10:43.600 --> 10:45.770
You're feeling unbelievable
pain and rage.

10:46.360 --> 10:49.440
How do you think I felt about
the sandbenders when they stole Appa?

10:50.150 --> 10:51.940
How do you think I felt
about the Fire Nation

10:52.030 --> 10:53.820
when I found out what happened
to my people?

10:54.160 --> 10:55.530
ZUKO: She needs this, Aang.

10:55.660 --> 10:58.240
This is about getting closure
and justice.

10:58.370 --> 10:59.620
I don't think so.

10:59.740 --> 11:01.500
I think it's about
getting revenge.

11:01.620 --> 11:02.830
KATARA: Fine, maybe it is.

11:02.960 --> 11:04.750
Maybe that's what I need.

11:04.870 --> 11:06.750
Maybe that's what he deserves.

11:06.880 --> 11:09.130
Katara, you sound like Jet.

11:09.250 --> 11:10.460
It's not the same.

11:10.670 --> 11:11.960
Jet attacked the innocent.

11:12.170 --> 11:14.180
This man, he's a monster.

11:14.430 --> 11:16.220
Katara, she was my mother too.

11:16.470 --> 11:18.550
But I think Aang might be right.

11:19.050 --> 11:20.890
Then you didn't love her
the way I did.

11:21.180 --> 11:22.470
Katara...

11:23.810 --> 11:27.310
The monks used to say that revenge
is like a two-headed rat viper.

11:27.900 --> 11:30.900
While you watch your enemy go down,
you're being poisoned yourself.

11:31.570 --> 11:34.280
That's cute, but this isn't
air temple preschool.

11:34.700 --> 11:36.110
It's the real world.

11:36.240 --> 11:38.160
Now that I know
he's out there...

11:38.280 --> 11:40.120
Now that I know
we can find him...

11:40.240 --> 11:41.870
I feel like I have no choice.

11:42.410 --> 11:44.660
Katara, you do have a choice.

11:44.960 --> 11:46.210
Forgiveness.

11:46.460 --> 11:48.210
That's the same as
doing nothing.

11:48.540 --> 11:50.130
No, it's not.

11:50.420 --> 11:53.800
It's easy to do nothing,
but it's hard to forgive.

11:53.920 --> 11:57.180
It's not just hard,
it's impossible.

12:07.770 --> 12:09.980
So you were just gonna
take Appa anyway?

12:10.940 --> 12:11.940
Yes.

12:12.150 --> 12:14.440
It's okay, because I forgive you.

12:15.860 --> 12:17.450
That give you any ideas?

12:17.610 --> 12:19.110
Don't try to stop us.

12:19.490 --> 12:21.200
I wasn't planning to.

12:21.330 --> 12:23.120
This is a journey
you need to take.

12:23.240 --> 12:25.040
You need to face this man.

12:27.250 --> 12:30.290
But when you do,
please don't choose revenge.

12:30.540 --> 12:33.460
Let your anger out,
and then let it go.

12:34.000 --> 12:35.130
Forgive him.

12:35.300 --> 12:38.510
Okay, we'll be sure to do that,
guru goody-goody.

12:38.760 --> 12:40.260
Thanks for understanding, Aang.

12:40.470 --> 12:41.510
Yip-yip.

12:42.180 --> 12:43.510
( APPA GROANING )

12:43.890 --> 12:45.640
You know, you're pretty wise
for a kid.

12:46.350 --> 12:47.480
Thanks, Sokka.

12:47.560 --> 12:49.850
Usually it's annoying, but
right now I'm just impressed.

12:50.190 --> 12:51.560
I appreciate that.

12:51.860 --> 12:53.770
So can I borrow Momo for a week?

12:54.070 --> 12:55.150
Why do you need Momo?

12:55.280 --> 12:56.440
( HUMS ) I don't know.

12:59.660 --> 13:02.370
ZUKO: We need to find the
fire navy communication tower.

13:02.660 --> 13:05.580
All the navy's movements are
coordinated by messenger hawk.

13:05.950 --> 13:08.660
And every tower has to be up to date
on where everyone is deployed.

13:09.290 --> 13:11.170
KATARA: <i>So once we find</i>
<i>the communication tower</i>

13:11.250 --> 13:13.380
<i>we bust in and take
the information we need.</i>

13:13.840 --> 13:15.130
ZUKO: <i>Not exactly.</i>

13:15.210 --> 13:17.720
<i>We need to be stealthy
and make sure no one spots us.</i>

13:18.130 --> 13:21.890
<i>Otherwise, they'll warn the southern
raiders long before we reach them.</i>

13:31.400 --> 13:33.400
( DOOR CREAKS )

13:47.700 --> 13:50.160
Okay, southern raiders.

13:52.330 --> 13:55.340
Bam, on patrol
near Whaletail Island.

13:56.170 --> 13:57.960
Whaletail Island,
here we come.

13:59.510 --> 14:01.840
( APPA GROANS )

14:06.970 --> 14:08.180
You should get some rest.

14:08.520 --> 14:09.810
We'll be there in a few hours.

14:10.310 --> 14:11.600
You'll need all your strength.

14:12.060 --> 14:13.770
Oh, don't you worry
about my strength.

14:13.900 --> 14:15.020
I have plenty.

14:15.360 --> 14:17.900
I'm not the helpless little girl
I was when they came.

14:22.030 --> 14:24.740
I'm going to find mom.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.500
Mom!

14:31.580 --> 14:33.120
MOTHER: Just let her go...

14:33.210 --> 14:35.080
and I'll give you
the information you want.

14:35.420 --> 14:37.750
You heard your mother...
Get out of here!

14:38.130 --> 14:40.010
Mom, I'm scared.

14:40.210 --> 14:41.380
Go find your dad, sweetie.

14:41.510 --> 14:42.510
I'll handle this.

14:50.430 --> 14:52.310
KATARA: <i>I ran</i>
<i>as fast as I could.</i>

14:52.480 --> 14:54.100
Dad, dad!

14:54.190 --> 14:55.980
Please, I think mom's
in trouble!

14:56.270 --> 14:57.440
There's a man in our house.

14:57.770 --> 14:58.820
Kya!

15:02.740 --> 15:04.410
KATARA: But we were too late.

15:05.110 --> 15:07.070
When we got there,
the man was gone...

15:07.660 --> 15:09.030
And so was she.

15:09.540 --> 15:11.160
Your mother was a brave woman.

15:13.790 --> 15:14.870
I know.

15:20.380 --> 15:22.630
There, see those
sea raven flags?

15:26.510 --> 15:28.140
ZUKO: It's the southern raiders.

15:28.350 --> 15:29.890
Let's do this.

15:37.860 --> 15:39.860
So there I was, and I was like,
you know, it was...

15:39.980 --> 15:41.440
( SCREAMS )

15:53.120 --> 15:54.370
( SCREAMING )

15:57.370 --> 15:59.210
( APPA SNORTS )

16:01.170 --> 16:02.750
( SCREAMS )

16:06.430 --> 16:07.430
( MAN GRUNTS )

16:12.310 --> 16:13.970
This is it, Katara.

16:14.060 --> 16:15.560
Are you ready to face him?

16:18.440 --> 16:19.440
( ROARS )

16:32.030 --> 16:33.240
Who are you?

16:33.330 --> 16:34.540
You don't remember her?

16:34.620 --> 16:36.370
You will soon, trust me.

16:40.080 --> 16:41.290
What's...

16:41.380 --> 16:43.340
( GRUNTING )

16:44.210 --> 16:45.550
Happening to me?

16:47.170 --> 16:48.340
( GROANS )

16:51.970 --> 16:53.100
Think back.

16:53.260 --> 16:56.060
Think back to your last raid
on the southern water tribe.

16:56.770 --> 16:58.600
I don't know what
you're talking about.

16:58.690 --> 17:00.060
Please, I don't know.

17:00.770 --> 17:02.020
Don't lie!

17:02.230 --> 17:05.070
You look her in the eye and you tell me
you don't remember what you did.

17:15.120 --> 17:16.200
It's not him.

17:17.870 --> 17:19.080
( GRUNTS )

17:19.670 --> 17:20.870
He's not the man.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.000
What?

17:22.080 --> 17:23.210
What do you mean he's not?

17:23.380 --> 17:24.880
He's the leader of
the southern raiders.

17:24.960 --> 17:26.300
He has to be the guy.

17:31.010 --> 17:32.260
( GRUNTING )

17:32.340 --> 17:34.640
If you're not the man
we're looking for, who is?

17:35.310 --> 17:37.060
You must be looking for Yon Rha.

17:37.390 --> 17:39.230
He retired four years ago.

17:51.360 --> 17:55.200
Yon Rha, you lazy piece of work,
I need something.

17:55.660 --> 17:56.990
Yes, mother.

17:57.490 --> 17:58.700
What is it?

17:58.870 --> 18:02.170
The tomato-carrot from your
garden are too hard for my gums.

18:02.370 --> 18:04.210
I need something soft and juicy.

18:04.920 --> 18:07.550
Would you like something else
from the garden?

18:07.750 --> 18:09.050
I would be happy to...

18:09.170 --> 18:10.510
Forget your stupid garden!

18:11.010 --> 18:14.390
Get your grimy heinie to the market
and buy me some real food.

18:17.810 --> 18:21.390
( THUNDER RUMBLING FAINTLY )

18:21.640 --> 18:24.520
( WIND CHIMES RINGING )

18:30.900 --> 18:32.150
Hello?

18:32.530 --> 18:34.110
Did you see someone?

18:44.460 --> 18:45.460
Hello?

18:45.670 --> 18:46.840
Is someone there?

18:50.050 --> 18:51.300
That was him.

18:51.420 --> 18:53.300
That was the monster.

18:58.600 --> 19:01.480
( THUNDER RUMBLING )

19:05.900 --> 19:07.980
Nobody sneaks up on me
without getting burned.

19:19.410 --> 19:20.790
( GRUNTS )

19:25.790 --> 19:27.670
We weren't behind the bush.

19:28.710 --> 19:31.000
And I wouldn't try
firebending again.

19:31.760 --> 19:34.880
Whoever you are, take my money,
take whatever you want.

19:35.090 --> 19:36.590
I'll cooperate.

19:38.010 --> 19:39.680
Do you know who I am?

19:40.310 --> 19:42.520
No... I'm not sure.

19:42.890 --> 19:45.600
Oh, you better remember me
like your life depends on it.

19:45.890 --> 19:47.770
Why don't you take
a closer look?

19:48.310 --> 19:52.280
Yes, yes, I remember you now.

19:53.070 --> 19:54.990
You're the little
water tribe girl.

19:55.360 --> 19:57.030
( THUNDER CRASHES )

19:57.110 --> 19:59.620
Just let her go and I'll give
you the information you want.

19:59.950 --> 20:01.160
You heard your mother.

20:01.450 --> 20:03.040
Get out of here.

20:03.120 --> 20:05.000
Mom, I'm scared.

20:05.160 --> 20:06.580
Go find your dad, sweetie.

20:06.750 --> 20:08.080
I'll handle this.

20:11.460 --> 20:14.590
Now tell me...
Who is it?

20:15.010 --> 20:16.880
Who's the waterbender?

20:17.130 --> 20:19.680
There are no waterbenders here.

20:19.890 --> 20:22.760
The Fire Nation took them
all away a long time ago.

20:22.890 --> 20:23.930
You're lying.

20:24.180 --> 20:29.150
My source says there's one waterbender
left in the southern water tribe.

20:29.270 --> 20:32.610
We're not leaving
until we find the waterbender.

20:32.820 --> 20:36.240
If I tell you, do you promise to leave
the rest of the village alone?

20:37.240 --> 20:38.700
Mm.

20:39.820 --> 20:42.280
It's me... Take me
as your prisoner.

20:42.700 --> 20:45.750
I'm afraid I'm not
taking prisoners today.

20:48.330 --> 20:49.330
( GULPS )

20:50.000 --> 20:51.000
( THUNDER CRASHES )

20:51.080 --> 20:52.130
She lied to you.

20:52.210 --> 20:54.210
She was protecting
the last waterbender.

20:54.300 --> 20:55.300
What?

20:55.460 --> 20:56.510
Who?

20:57.720 --> 20:58.720
Me!

21:12.190 --> 21:13.360
( GRUNTS )

21:14.190 --> 21:15.320
( WHIMPERS )

21:28.830 --> 21:32.670
I did a bad thing, I know I did,
and you deserve revenge.

21:32.790 --> 21:34.500
So why don't you take my mother?

21:34.590 --> 21:35.750
That would be fair.

21:36.340 --> 21:39.300
I always wondered what kind of
person could do such a thing.

21:39.760 --> 21:42.640
But now that I see you,
I think I understand.

21:43.140 --> 21:46.770
There's just nothing inside you,
nothing at all.

21:47.060 --> 21:49.270
You're pathetic and sad
and empty.

21:49.350 --> 21:51.980
Please spare me. ( WHIMPERS )

21:52.350 --> 21:54.480
But as much as I hate you...

21:56.190 --> 21:57.860
I just can't do it.

22:04.450 --> 22:07.040
( YON RHA WHIMPERING )

22:17.460 --> 22:18.670
( APPA GROANS )

22:25.350 --> 22:27.140
Katara, are you okay?

22:28.220 --> 22:29.560
I'm doing fine.

22:30.930 --> 22:32.600
Zuko told me what you did.

22:32.980 --> 22:34.770
Or what you didn't do, I guess.

22:35.310 --> 22:36.400
I'm proud of you.

22:37.320 --> 22:38.530
I wanted to do it.

22:38.780 --> 22:42.030
I wanted to take out all my
anger at him, but I couldn't.

22:42.860 --> 22:45.570
I don't know if it's
because I'm too weak to do it

22:45.660 --> 22:48.030
or if it's because
I'm strong enough not to.

22:48.370 --> 22:49.660
AANG: You did the right thing.

22:49.870 --> 22:53.040
Forgiveness is the first step you have
to take to begin healing.

22:55.380 --> 22:58.750
But I didn't forgive him...
I'll never forgive him.

23:01.010 --> 23:03.170
But I am ready to forgive you.

23:10.020 --> 23:12.060
ZUKO: You were right
about what Katara needed.

23:12.680 --> 23:14.270
Violence wasn't the answer.

23:14.810 --> 23:16.150
It never is.

23:16.650 --> 23:18.650
Then I have a question for you.

23:19.730 --> 23:21.650
What are you gonna do
when you face my father?

23:33.250 --> 23:36.000
( MEN VOCALIZING RHYTHMICALLY )
